reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Tiny and capable
reviews.reviewText: I knew I was getting something small, but this thing is tiny. 4.25x4.75x1.5 ~. It's very light, too. Mine came with 16 gb RAM and a 500 gb SSD. It's very fast. I hooked it up to my smart TV to stream YouTube TV. The TV's wifi capabilities were no longer able to deliver a smooth stream on some stations. The Mini receives the WIFI signal for the TV, delivering the data to the TV via the included HDMI cable without a hiccup. Setup was simple, and my only problem was my TV picture brightness dimmed significantly, and there was no brightness setting on the PC for the monitor. Finally discovered that the TV reverted to what it calls Standard Mode when I hooked the Mini up to it. Changed the TV's mode back to Dynamic, and all was perfect. I plan to get a small BT keyboard to handle any needed input from my easy chair, such as logging in or searching the internet. A small mouse is my TV remote.

The Mini PC with Windows 11 Pro and Intel 11th Gen N5095 processor has proven to be a powerful and versatile computing solution in a compact form factor. With its impressive hardware specifications and connectivity options, it offers a great computing experience for both work and entertainment. Here's a comprehensive review of the Mini PC:Pros:Powerful Processor: The Intel 11th Gen N5095 processor with speeds of up to 2.9 GHz ensures snappy performance and efficient multitasking capabilities. It handles demanding tasks with ease and provides a smooth computing experience.Ample RAM and Storage Options: The availability of 8GB or 16GB DDR4 RAM and 256GB or 512GB M.2 SATA SSD (with support for up to 2TB) offers excellent flexibility for different user needs. The fast DDR4 RAM and spacious SSD storage contribute to quick boot times and responsive application performance.Compact and Space-Saving: The Mini Desktop Computer's compact size makes it ideal for small spaces and clutter-free workstations. It can easily fit behind a monitor or be placed discreetly on a desk, saving valuable desk real estate.Dual HDMI and 4K UHD Support: The support for dual HDMI outputs and 4K UHD resolution allows for connecting multiple monitors and enjoying high-definition content, making it suitable for productivity and multimedia purposes.Fast Connectivity: The Mini PC supports USB 3.0, Bluetooth 4.0, and 2.4G+5G WiFi, providing fast data transfer, seamless connections to peripherals, and reliable wireless networking.Cons:No Discrete Graphics: While the Mini PC's integrated graphics are sufficient for most everyday tasks and multimedia playback, it may not be suitable for graphics-intensive applications or gaming at high settings. A discrete graphics option would have been a welcome addition for more demanding users.Limited Upgradeability: Due to the compact design, the Mini PC's upgrade options might be limited. Upgrading components like the processor or graphics might not be as straightforward as with traditional desktop PCs.Conclusion:The Mini PC with Windows 11 Pro and Intel 11th Gen N5095 processor is a highly capable computing solution in a compact package. Its powerful processor, ample RAM, and fast SSD storage ensure efficient performance for various tasks. The support for dual HDMI and 4K UHD resolution is a boon for productivity and multimedia enthusiasts. While the lack of discrete graphics and limited upgradeability might be a consideration for certain users, it doesn't detract from the Mini PC's overall value and performance. If you're looking for a space-saving and versatile computing solution with modern features, the Mini PC with Windows 11 Pro and Intel 11th Gen N5095 processor is a reliable choice for both work and entertainment needs.
